<author><name><![CDATA[Dwedit]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-08-24T10:01:23-07:00</updated>
<published>2011-08-24T10:01:23-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8057&amp;p=83084#p83084</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8057&amp;p=83084#p83084"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Crystal Mines Source Code Released]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8057&amp;p=83084#p83084"><![CDATA[
Using reg OAMADDR as a way of crude OAM cycling has been done before, but it's obvious that that documenation didn't know about all sprites past the  8th sprite being discarded on every scanline no matter what.  When they mention the first 2 sprites disappearing, that means they wrote a higher value to OAMADDR, then uploaded the sprite table.  So that means early sprites instead become late sprites, so they are discarded.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Wed Aug 24, 2011 10:01 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
